StreamTokenizer - Class in java.base
The StreamTokenizer class takes an input stream and parses it into "tokens", allowing the tokens to be read one at a time.
StreamTokenizer(InputStream) - Constructor for class java.base.StreamTokenizer
Deprecated.
Prefer creating StreamTokenizer with the Reader

An example instantiation if you have an input stream: 

 Reader r = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(is));
   StreamTokenizer st = new StreamTokenizer(r);
StreamTokenizer(Reader) - Constructor for class java.base.StreamTokenizer
Creates a stream tokenizer to parse the given character stream.
sval - Variable in class java.base.StreamTokenizer
